  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd : \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b92\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd - '\u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe \u0b95\u0bcb \u0b95\u0bae' \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc2\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Let's Fear Night Attacks: Let's Unite Again - 'Kota Ko Kama' Protesters Say",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "Following the early morning attack last Friday, Kota Ko Kama was deserted yesterday and security was beefed up in the area near the President's Secretariat.",
        "However, some of the protestors in the area told Veerakesari that they will not be afraid of nightly attacks and that even if there is a gap or interruption in this protest, the protest will continue until they achieve their goal.",
        "In the wake of the severe economic crisis, the people of the country united and carried out a self-insurgency struggle for more than 100 days, Colombo, empty-faced 'Kota Ko Kama' was surrounded by a large group of policemen, tri-armies and special task forces yesterday morning, and a brutal attack was made on the protestors, lawyers and journalists there. captured.",
        "While the protestors had already decided to issue an official announcement to withdraw from the Presidential Secretariat and dissolve the 'Kota Ko Kama' protest site at 2 pm on Friday, the suppression of the people's protest by the iron fist of the army had created massive international shocks even after the swearing in of Ranil Wickramasinghe as the 8th President of the country had not even completed 24 hours.",
        "Apart from that, all roads leading to the Presidential Secretariat were blocked by the security forces and media persons were also denied entry into the area.",
        "Against this backdrop, security around the Presidential Secretariat was strengthened yesterday and Saturday. In particular, barricades have been put up to prevent entry into the area and police, army and special task forces have been engaged in security operations.",
        "Meanwhile, yesterday, Kalimugattidal, 'Kota Ko Kama' was found deserted and only a few people could be seen in the tents there.",
        "However, some of the protestors there told Veerakesari that they will not be afraid of nightly attacks and that even if there is a gap or interruption in this protest, the protest will continue until they reach their goal."
      ],
